description:
Malmö's International Improv Players (MIIP) is now finally on Meetup...

Welcome to the colorful and fun world of Improv!

Improv (also known as Improvisational theatre or Impro) is the art of playing different games in the moment, without preparations or script. The improvisers are acting, directing themselves, writing the plot and interacting with each other all at the same time without previous planning. It is all about being positive and having plenty of fun together!

Improv offers a chance to relax, really be yourself, bring out your inner child and drop your defenses in a safe and positive enviromement. We, kind of improvise all the time in real life, we don't plan every conversation and interaction that is going to happen to us during the day. Many of the best bits of life are totaly spontaneous, and this is what we try to recreate in a more creative way in Improv.

Improv also improves intuition, trains creativity and teamwork, gives more confidence in all sorts of social situations. Improv helps even with business skills by training your mind to think quickly and react to unexpected situations. Can you believe that?!

We are a group of positive, laugh-loving and open-minded improv addicts from all around the world. We have been meeting for couple of years now, twice a week in central Malmö. We often invite professional improvisers or experienced improv-friends in order to develop our skills. Once in a while we give performances in cooperation with MAF (Malmö Amatörteater Forum). We are always open for new ideas and new enthusiastic improvisers.

Join us and a excitiiiiing new world will open up for you!!!

Keep an eye on us even on Facebook ;) https://www.facebook.com/groups/1788224644737991/

If you feel even more proactive, feel free to join our organizing team :)

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
This group wants to propose a series of games and exercises to create a nice evening of exploration and discovery by the hand of Theater.

Acting is playing. Playing is joy. Joy is freedom. Freedom is being unblocked.

The only barrier between the actor and the expression is the blocks that he has.

Free expression, which means in this case, playful expression is the base for acting. The rest is practice, technic, and each ones resources and interests.

Being free of blocks is being free of acting or thinking through the mind. We want people to realize that to follow the body impulses and not the mind impulses (thoughts) free the actor from blocks. In this workshop, I will propose many different exercises, games and improvisations that will give a chance to the actors to realize this for themselves. By making mistakes and failing in the desire of expressing something to the audience, the actor realizes that the only intelligence that can help in this purpose comes from the body (intuitive) and not from the intellect.

If you ask the mind, how does the “blue” color moves?, or if you ask the mind to move like Picasso’s Guernica, the mind will block itself, or will come out with a very intellectual, and “cold” approach which is not interesting for Theater.

Now, if you ask the body, or I should say, if you let the body with its imagination explore into this question, it will come out with an expression that will be different in everyone of us and that cannot be evaluated into good or bad (as it is its own exploration). This expression will be interesting for the audience (in this case the rest of actors in the workshop). Because it comes out of a common place everyone will connect in some way or the other with it. Now this exploration can only be done out of joy and playfulness.


We could divide the evening in to 3 different sections:

Awareness and awakening of the senses. 

Exploration of the imagination of the body

Play: Scenes, improvisation, sketches, comic numbers

For all kinds of artistic people with artistic interests or just curiosity.

For more information contact me: danielramoslorenzo@gmail.com

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
What do we do each week? We work on all aspects of producing a play from the beginning to the performance at the end.

Who is it open to? All people in the area who speak English to a comfortable level.

What if I have no drama experience? Not a problem

What if I have lots of drama experience? Great, you are welcome and we offer a great chance to keep your skills up and connect you with other actors/writers/theatre enthusiasts in the area.

What we don't offer? We don't offer Swedish language skills, we don't offer any payment or jobs and we don't provide any visas or support for people wanting to be resident in Sweden.

What we do? We offer a fun group environment of various internationals and great people a chance to give something back to the local arts and culture.

Is there any parts in the current play left? No sadly, but we also have absentees so need people to read all the time so come down and see what we are about.  When we get enough newcomers we can start on a new group and new show for those people.

What if I don't want to be on stage? That is fine we welcome all sorts help from script writers, makeup, stage management, sound and light you name it we need it.

What if I don't have theatre skills but have other stage skills? Then please come meet with us we are always looking for ways to develop our performance and working with other artists like musicians, dancers, etc would be fun.

What if I want to do improv? Then I recommend our good friends over at https://www.meetup.com/Malmo-Improvisatorium/

What if I just want to watch english theatre? Then keep an eye on this page for future meetups or our facebook group On Stage Skåne.

What if I have any questions/queries? Then please drop me a direct message on meetup.

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Have you ever imagined what would it be like to be completely uninhibited and freely create spontaneous drama and comedy... Or perhaps imagine yourself, a fully grown adult, being given a permission to act like a little kid again, when everything you create on stage is as real as the bright shiny red ball that someone now is bouncing on the floor as we speak :)

This is exactly how life goes here, at Malmö Improvisatorium! Silly laughs, enchanting improv games and a fantastic atmosphere are guaranteed to open up your endless flow of fantasy. We are about theatre, acting and improvising. It is a perfect place to forget the 'real' world in exchange for fun, inspiration and happy improvisation feelings.

Malmö Improvisatorium is a very lively place:

-We always welcome you to our cozy universe of improvisation theatre. All that we ask is that you come with a positive attitude, a willingness to say yes, and explore a bit of social discomfort...Think of it like a runner's high, actually pretty awesome if you ask us!

-At some point you may discover that you actually may want to become a good improviser. Coincidentally, we have a regular group of highly skilled and amazing improv artists. And you are welcome to join this infinite fun! By the way, we pay a great deal of attention to the skills we wish to develop as a group. If you are already an experienced improviser, this is probably a great place ;)

-We like to perform in public and you may see us sometimes on stage, or performing in a bar, or maybe even in the street or on the beach. We prove over and over that everyone has a talent to improvise and even if you have never improvised before, who knows, maybe one day you will find yourself on stage. Sometimes we have dedicated series of classes intended for the performing improvisers.

-We also like to shoot short movies. We do it in a fruitful collaboration with a talented film director. We have proved a simple formula, which goes as Improvisers+Camera+Enthusiasm=Fun, Beauty and many other miracles.


There are some guidelines to make improv a fun and rewarding experience for every player involved. They are well summarised in 13 "maxims" (rules) of improv: 

1. Say yes

2. Don't prepare

3. Just show up

4. Start anywhere

5. Be average

6. Pay attention

7. Face the facts

8. Stay on course

9. Wake up to the gifts

10. Make mistakes, please

11. Act now

12. Take care of each other

13. Enjoy the ride

(from the book "Improv Wisdom" by Patricia Ryan Madsen)


In addition, to make this a happy constructive experience:

1. Be safe

2. Be nice 


Ready, Set, Go!!!

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Malmö's International Improv Players (MIIP) is now finally on Meetup...

Welcome to the colorful and fun world of Improv!

Improv (also known as Improvisational theatre or Impro) is the art of playing different games in the moment, without preparations or script. The improvisers are acting, directing themselves, writing the plot and interacting with each other all at the same time without previous planning. It is all about being positive and having plenty of fun together!

Improv offers a chance to relax, really be yourself, bring out your inner child and drop your defenses in a safe and positive enviromement. We, kind of improvise all the time in real life, we don't plan every conversation and interaction that is going to happen to us during the day. Many of the best bits of life are totaly spontaneous, and this is what we try to recreate in a more creative way in Improv.

Improv also improves intuition, trains creativity and teamwork, gives more confidence in all sorts of social situations. Improv helps even with business skills by training your mind to think quickly and react to unexpected situations. Can you believe that?!

We are a group of positive, laugh-loving and open-minded improv addicts from all around the world. We have been meeting for couple of years now, twice a week in central Malmö. We often invite professional improvisers or experienced improv-friends in order to develop our skills. Once in a while we give performances in cooperation with MAF (Malmö Amatörteater Forum). We are always open for new ideas and new enthusiastic improvisers.

Join us and a excitiiiiing new world will open up for you!!!

Keep an eye on us even on Facebook ;) https://www.facebook.com/groups/1788224644737991/

description:
The Stockholm Drawing Meetup is a group that has been up and running since April 2015 by volunteers, with the intention of meeting and getting creative together and socialize.

The Stockholm Drawing Meetup’s core goal is to organize art related and fun activities by promoting the cooperation and collaborative work, while keeping in mind constantly the human aspects and needs.

If you like to draw, paint, sketch, etc. or have done so in the past and would like to share the experience in a meetup-setup and have fun at the same time, this group is for you.

This applies to pencil/coal, water color or acrylic/oil or any other medium.

You do not have to be a professional to join but you must have an interest in creating art.

Our members have different concepts of art and participate with different goals. There are members of all the levels, from very beginners, hobbyists to professionals.

In general it is up to you which technique/s or medium to use at every activity.

If you would like to send a particular suggestion for activities or you desire to host an event, don't hesitate to contact any of the co-organizers.

As the group has grown up to reach almost 900 members, from different cultures and backgrounds, it has been considered the need to set up some rules, so that the organization becomes easier and everyone that wants to participate can do it freely, safe and comfortably.

Please read carefully our organization policy and its updatings sited at the forum, and make sure this is something you are prepared to abide:

https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51143584

https://www.meetup.com/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51306390

Thanks! <3

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
This is a meetup group for the creative people of Stockholm who are looking for companionship of other creatives. We aim for a simple sense of community to begin with, and if people are inspired, perhaps some collaboration can happen.

Meetups are held on a regular basis where we engage in conversations and discussions about a predetermined topic of interest.

People of all creative fields are welcome to join. Whether if you are into creative writing, filmmaking, painting, photography, performing, designing, or just have a general interest in creativity, we would love to meet you. It is a rich mix and makes for a lively meetup!

With a healthy dose of “fika”, we encourage and inspire each other to explore our creativity by fostering a vibrant space that is supportive and non judgmental.

Things to expect:

• A friendly group of supportive people to hang out with on a regular basis.

• A safe environment for new creatives and established ones.

• Fika!

Things that we avoid:

• Judgment calls. This is a friendly community where we can find support and camaraderie.

• Drama. Let's leave the drama in the fictional stories!

If this sounds like a fun interesting group, feel free to join and come to one of our meetings!

P.S. We have a private Facebook group, please join it if you have attended an event.
name: Stockholm Creative People Meetups

category.name: fine arts/culture
description: This group is designed to mediate deeper experiences and understanding of contemporary visual culture. If you're interested in art, but don't always "get it" this group's aim is to contextualize an artwork, performance, or exhibition, through a shared moderated dialogue between members. As a community we may read a text together and discuss it before seeing an exhibition, we may attend a lecture, participate in a workshop, create an object together, any exercise that helps us to more fully appreciate and comprehend visual culture and interdisciplinary practice. We will normally have a "Prep" meetup and then an excursion to go see actual works. Suggestions are welcomed and different members could lead a project, there's no hierarchy. We won't act as museum tour guides or educators, this is a participatory network.

description:
Welcome to a super fun class on improvised singing. It´s just what it sounds like: we create new melodies and lyrics on the spot, using techniques from improv theater and combining it with music theory. This will be two hours of solid fun and constant singing, and you will most definitely break away from your safe zone while making new friends. 

The pianist for this workshop is the fantastic Annika Olsson. Annika has many years of experience working with classes is musical improv. You might for instance have heard and seen her recently in the show Lost in Translation at Boulevardteatern!

Katja Hvenmark-Nilsson has studied musical improv at the Magnet Theater in New York, Improverket and GBG impro. You might have seen her recently on stage with  Achtung Improv or International Theater of Stockholm, where she also teaches drop-ins.

description:
Vad gör vi? 

Vi på Design Lab Sweden genomför kostnadsfria inspirerande öppna workshops. Dessa riktar sig till kreatörer, designers och konstintresserade. Hos oss finner alla en plats där man samlas och gör saker tillsammans i flera olika teman i workshopform.


Organisation

Design Lab Sweden och Stockholm Läns Museum - Slöjd Sthlm

Design Lab Sweden är en ideell organisation som arbetar för att stimulera designintresse och utveckling inom form & design i Sverige. Vi som driver DLS är volontärer och studerar inom konst & design. 


Gästföreläsare 

Olika gästföreläsare vid varje tillfälle 

_____________________________

What we do?

We at Design Lab Sweden carry out free of charge inspirational workshops. These are aimed at creators, designers and artists. With us you will find a place where you can gather and do things together in several different workshop themes.


Organization

Design Lab Sweden and Stockholm Museum - Crafts Sthlm


Design Lab Sweden is a nonprofit organization that works to stimulate design interests and development in form & design in Sweden. We are based in Stockholm.

We who run DLS are volunteers, young professionals and students in art and design.

We are based in Stockholm.


-Our Lab meetings are twice a month. Every other Tuesday -


This group is for you.... 


Who have/are a passionate creative heart, designer, Illustrator etc…. 


Who want to keep inspired 


Who want to share his/her knowledge with other creatives


Who know that our field keeps updating all the time 


Who want to share ideas & connect with new creators. 


Note! 

Since many of us are working or studying. We have planned to hold our workshops at the following time below

Every other Tuesday 18:00 - 21:00

If it’s during weekend 12:00 – 15:00


Contact 

Email claudia@designlabsweden.se 


Stay tuned!

https://www.meetup.com/Design-lab-Sweden/

https://www.facebook.com/designlabsweden2017/ 

https://www.instagram.com/designlabsweden/

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Do you find it challenging to speak Swedish outside of class? Would you like to practice your Swedish in a friendly and safe environment? Are you curious to try a new and fun way of learning? Then this is the workshop for you!

Research shows that laughing makes it easier to learn and remember new information, and one of our favourite ways to laugh is improvised theatre (improv). That is why we have created this group; to provide an opportunity for you to practice your Swedish outside of class, in a new and unconventional way that involves lots of laughing.

Together, we will do different improv games and exercises, in simple Swedish, allowing you to use your current vocabulary as well as expand it further. One of the bases of improv is to ”celebrate your failures” which means that the classes will allow you to make mistakes in a safe environment, so that it’s easier to relax while strengthening your Swedish language muscles!

For those who attend the drop-ins, we would also like to give you the chance to see an improv show and therefore give you a free ticket to one of our ”Improkavalkad” shows in January, played in Swedish.  There will also be occasions when we go out for drinks together after class.

Cost for drop- in classes in January and first class in February: FREE

Mid-February we will start with a class that extends over 6 weeks where we will have themed classes focusing on different specific areas and exercises each week. Examples of themes are: characters, storytelling and being a good listener. 

You do not need any previous theatre or improv experience, however a basic level of understanding and speaking Swedish is required.

Like us on Facebook and don't miss out on cool stuff: https://www.facebook.com/Impro-p%C3%A5-l%C3...

All the best,

Stockholms Improvisationsteater

description:
This meet up group is for:
Artists, painters, print makers, sculptors, conceptual artists, hobby artists, graphic designers, etc.
Gallery folks, collectors, enthusiasts, historians.... international artists, art students, art supporters, art marketers ...

No event is too big or too small, Drawing and drinking tea at the kitchen table or going to Louisiana. And not necessesarily big known thiings, rather original nice things down to earth. preferably with broad cultural and global aspects, Russian, Arabian, armenian, inuit, indian, chinese. You name it. Many languages, many ethnies, many techniques and tastes as well. We cover Copenhagen and Nordsjællland and malmö as well.


We get together to:
discuss techniques, teach one another, share critiques, and offer gallery/exhibiting advice. To go to openings, exhibits and create events (like groups shows) of interest to the group.
So when you find out about an art event or want to share your artistic views with us, please use the Idea Tab of the Meetup site. Thanks.

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
A very warm welcome to the Copenhagen Theatre Circle (CTC) Meetup Group! The CTC is an English-language amateur theatre company that has been performing high-quality theatre in Copenhagen since 1968. We usually put on three full-scale shows each year, in the spring, autumn and winter (the winter production being a British pantomime). We hold open auditions for our shows, which means that anyone is free to audition. Apart from actors, our membership includes directors, stage managers, designers, technicians, costume people, set builders, PR people and a myriad of others who make our shows work.

If you want to become a CTC member and join us in one or more of these activities then please go to our website at www.ctcircle.dk and click on ”Get Involved” in the top menu. 

Besides our regular Meetups, we encourage our members to be creative and come with their own project proposals. These can take any form as long as it has something to do with the performing arts. So, for example, if you’re burning to perform that play you’ve just written, put together a project and we’ll most likely support you! Don't be shy! Come along and have some fun. You'll meet great people and who knows, you might just find yourself under the bright lights one day ...

There are many ways to keep an eye on what we're up to, either follow us here on Meet Up, keep an eye on our website (www.ctcircle.dk), Like us on Facebook (https://www.facebook.com/ctcircle/?ref=ts&fref=ts) or even follow us on Twitter (https://twitter.com/ctcircledk) 

We look forward to seeing you at one of our future events.
name: Copenhagen Theatre Circle (CTC) Meet-Up Group

description:
What do we do each week? We work on all aspects of producing a play from the beginning to the performance at the end.

Who is it open to? All people in the area who speak English to a comfortable level.

What if I have no drama experience? Not a problem

What if I have lots of drama experience? Great, you are welcome and we offer a great chance to keep your skills up and connect you with other actors/writers/theatre enthusiasts in the area.

What we don't offer? We don't offer Swedish language skills, we don't offer any payment or jobs and we don't provide any visas or support for people wanting to be resident in Sweden.

What we do? We offer a fun group environment of various internationals and great people a chance to give something back to the local arts and culture.

Is there any parts in the current play left? No sadly, but we also have absentees so need people to read all the time so come down and see what we are about.  When we get enough newcomers we can start on a new group and new show for those people.

What if I don't want to be on stage? That is fine we welcome all sorts help from script writers, makeup, stage management, sound and light you name it we need it.

What if I don't have theatre skills but have other stage skills? Then please come meet with us we are always looking for ways to develop our performance and working with other artists like musicians, dancers, etc would be fun.

What if I want to do improv? Then I recommend our good friends over at https://www.meetup.com/Malmo-Improvisatorium/

What if I just want to watch english theatre? Then keep an eye on this page for future meetups or our facebook group On Stage Skåne.

What if I have any questions/queries? Then please drop me a direct message on meetup.
name: Malmö Lund Theatre Meetup

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Have you ever imagined what would it be like to be completely uninhibited and freely create spontaneous drama and comedy... Or perhaps imagine yourself, a fully grown adult, being given a permission to act like a little kid again, when everything you create on stage is as real as the bright shiny red ball that someone now is bouncing on the floor as we speak :)

This is exactly how life goes here, at Malmö Improvisatorium! Silly laughs, enchanting improv games and a fantastic atmosphere are guaranteed to open up your endless flow of fantasy. We are about theatre, acting and improvising. It is a perfect place to forget the 'real' world in exchange for fun, inspiration and happy improvisation feelings.

Malmö Improvisatorium is a very lively place:

-We always welcome you to our cozy universe of improvisation theatre. All that we ask is that you come with a positive attitude, a willingness to say yes, and explore a bit of social discomfort...Think of it like a runner's high, actually pretty awesome if you ask us!

-At some point you may discover that you actually may want to become a good improviser. Coincidentally, we have a regular group of highly skilled and amazing improv artists. And you are welcome to join this infinite fun! By the way, we pay a great deal of attention to the skills we wish to develop as a group. If you are already an experienced improviser, this is probably a great place ;)

-We like to perform in public and you may see us sometimes on stage, or performing in a bar, or maybe even in the street or on the beach. We prove over and over that everyone has a talent to improvise and even if you have never improvised before, who knows, maybe one day you will find yourself on stage. Sometimes we have dedicated series of classes intended for the performing improvisers.

-We also like to shoot short movies. We do it in a fruitful collaboration with a talented film director. We have proved a simple formula, which goes as Improvisers+Camera+Enthusiasm=Fun, Beauty and many other miracles.


There are some guidelines to make improv a fun and rewarding experience for every player involved. They are well summarised in 13 "maxims" (rules) of improv: 

1. Say yes

2. Don't prepare

3. Just show up

4. Start anywhere

5. Be average

6. Pay attention

7. Face the facts

8. Stay on course

9. Wake up to the gifts

10. Make mistakes, please

11. Act now

12. Take care of each other

13. Enjoy the ride

(from the book "Improv Wisdom" by Patricia Ryan Madsen)


In addition, to make this a happy constructive experience:

1. Be safe

2. Be nice 


Ready, Set, Go!!!

description:
This group is for Copenhagen based artists of all types. This is an active networking group for A variety of artists, from fine artists to jewelry designers, photographers, videographers, performance artists, tattoo artists, painters and 3D artists. The Meetup sessions might involve life drawing sessions, gallery visits, workshops or group meetings for critiques (if wanted), brainstorming sessions and sharing of ideas or just sitting around talking about art or art events. Networking, giving each other advice, tutoring, workshops and a helping hand with promoting each other and cross-promoting is what this community should be about.

We encourage all members to share opportunities, techniques and information that might be helpful for an artistic career or hobby. It is also a great way to make friends with some similar interests!

The organizer of the group is Erika Stanley. Erika has been making a living from her art for over 25 years. She is a photographer (32 years), artist (35 years) and tattoo artist (23 years) who also founded and still runs a thriving tattoo studio in the Los Angeles area for the past 21 years (www.artandsoultattoos.com) she is currently in process of expanding her tattoo studio by opening a location one block away from Frederiksberg Metro and shopping center which includes a gallery to help local Copenhagen artists exhibit and sell their art (follow on Instagram @artandsoulgallery.dk or artandsoultattoos.dk or @erikafromamericatattoos) She really believes that for artists, art comes from the soul and is almost necessary for some souls to survive.

Erika's websites are: <br>Photography: <br>www.erikastanley.com <br>Arts & Publications: <br>www.erikastanleyarts.com <br>Tattooing: <br>www.erikafromamericatattoos.com

If anyone has any suggestions for meet ups, exhibits and interactions to help make this group more exciting, please feel free to contribute and send a message or post a discussion on the message board!

Join us on Facebook: <br>https://www.facebook.com/groups/1641077069260382/

Thanks for joining!

<br>

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Malmö's International Improv Players (MIIP) is now finally on Meetup...

Welcome to the colorful and fun world of Improv!

Improv (also known as Improvisational theatre or Impro) is the art of playing different games in the moment, without preparations or script. The improvisers are acting, directing themselves, writing the plot and interacting with each other all at the same time without previous planning. It is all about being positive and having plenty of fun together!

Improv offers a chance to relax, really be yourself, bring out your inner child and drop your defenses in a safe and positive enviromement. We, kind of improvise all the time in real life, we don't plan every conversation and interaction that is going to happen to us during the day. Many of the best bits of life are totaly spontaneous, and this is what we try to recreate in a more creative way in Improv.

Improv also improves intuition, trains creativity and teamwork, gives more confidence in all sorts of social situations. Improv helps even with business skills by training your mind to think quickly and react to unexpected situations. Can you believe that?!

We are a group of positive, laugh-loving and open-minded improv addicts from all around the world. We have been meeting for couple of years now, twice a week in central Malmö. We often invite professional improvisers or experienced improv-friends in order to develop our skills. Once in a while we give performances in cooperation with MAF (Malmö Amatörteater Forum). We are always open for new ideas and new enthusiastic improvisers.

Join us and a excitiiiiing new world will open up for you!!!

Keep an eye on us even on Facebook ;) https://www.facebook.com/groups/1788224644737991/

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
This group wants to propose a series of games and exercises to create a nice evening of exploration and discovery by the hand of Theater.

Acting is playing. Playing is joy. Joy is freedom. Freedom is being unblocked.

The only barrier between the actor and the expression is the blocks that he has.

Free expression, which means in this case, playful expression is the base for acting. The rest is practice, technic, and each ones resources and interests.

Being free of blocks is being free of acting or thinking through the mind. We want people to realize that to follow the body impulses and not the mind impulses (thoughts) free the actor from blocks. In this workshop, I will propose many different exercises, games and improvisations that will give a chance to the actors to realize this for themselves. By making mistakes and failing in the desire of expressing something to the audience, the actor realizes that the only intelligence that can help in this purpose comes from the body (intuitive) and not from the intellect.

If you ask the mind, how does the “blue” color moves?, or if you ask the mind to move like Picasso’s Guernica, the mind will block itself, or will come out with a very intellectual, and “cold” approach which is not interesting for Theater.

Now, if you ask the body, or I should say, if you let the body with its imagination explore into this question, it will come out with an expression that will be different in everyone of us and that cannot be evaluated into good or bad (as it is its own exploration). This expression will be interesting for the audience (in this case the rest of actors in the workshop). Because it comes out of a common place everyone will connect in some way or the other with it. Now this exploration can only be done out of joy and playfulness.


We could divide the evening in to 3 different sections:

Awareness and awakening of the senses. 

Exploration of the imagination of the body

Play: Scenes, improvisation, sketches, comic numbers

For all kinds of artistic people with artistic interests or just curiosity.

For more information contact me: danielramoslorenzo@gmail.com

description:
The Stockholm Drawing Meetup is a group that has been up and running since April 2015 by volunteers, with the intention of meeting and getting creative together and socialize.

The Stockholm Drawing Meetup’s core goal is to organize art related and fun activities by promoting the cooperation and collaborative work, while keeping in mind constantly the human aspects and needs.

If you like to draw, paint, sketch, etc. or have done so in the past and would like to share the experience in a meetup-setup and have fun at the same time, this group is for you.

This applies to pencil/coal, water color or acrylic/oil or any other medium.

You do not have to be a professional to join but you must have an interest in creating art.

Our members have different concepts of art and participate with different goals. There are members of all the levels, from very beginners, hobbyists to professionals.

In general it is up to you which technique/s or medium to use at every activity.

If you would like to send a particular suggestion for activities or you desire to host an event, don't hesitate to contact any of the co-organizers.

As the group has grown up to reach almost 900 members, from different cultures and backgrounds, it has been considered the need to set up some rules, so that the organization becomes easier and everyone that wants to participate can do it freely, safe and comfortably.

Please read carefully our organization policy and its updatings sited at the forum, and make sure this is something you are prepared to abide:

https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51143584

https://www.meetup.com/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51306390

Thanks! <3

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
This is a meetup group for the creative people of Stockholm who are looking for companionship of other creatives. We aim for a simple sense of community to begin with, and if people are inspired, perhaps some collaboration can happen.

Meetups are held on a regular basis where we engage in conversations and discussions about a predetermined topic of interest.

People of all creative fields are welcome to join. Whether if you are into creative writing, filmmaking, painting, photography, performing, designing, or just have a general interest in creativity, we would love to meet you. It is a rich mix and makes for a lively meetup!

With a healthy dose of “fika”, we encourage and inspire each other to explore our creativity by fostering a vibrant space that is supportive and non judgmental.

Things to expect:

• A friendly group of supportive people to hang out with on a regular basis.

• A safe environment for new creatives and established ones.

• Fika!

Things that we avoid:

• Judgment calls. This is a friendly community where we can find support and camaraderie.

• Drama. Let's leave the drama in the fictional stories!

If this sounds like a fun interesting group, feel free to join and come to one of our meetings!

P.S. We have a private Facebook group, please join it if you have attended an event.
name: Stockholm Creative People Meetups

category.name: fine arts/culture
description: This group is designed to mediate deeper experiences and understanding of contemporary visual culture. If you're interested in art, but don't always "get it" this group's aim is to contextualize an artwork, performance, or exhibition, through a shared moderated dialogue between members. As a community we may read a text together and discuss it before seeing an exhibition, we may attend a lecture, participate in a workshop, create an object together, any exercise that helps us to more fully appreciate and comprehend visual culture and interdisciplinary practice. We will normally have a "Prep" meetup and then an excursion to go see actual works. Suggestions are welcomed and different members could lead a project, there's no hierarchy. We won't act as museum tour guides or educators, this is a participatory network.

description:
Welcome to a super fun class on improvised singing. It´s just what it sounds like: we create new melodies and lyrics on the spot, using techniques from improv theater and combining it with music theory. This will be two hours of solid fun and constant singing, and you will most definitely break away from your safe zone while making new friends. 

The pianist for this workshop is the fantastic Annika Olsson. Annika has many years of experience working with classes is musical improv. You might for instance have heard and seen her recently in the show Lost in Translation at Boulevardteatern!

Katja Hvenmark-Nilsson has studied musical improv at the Magnet Theater in New York, Improverket and GBG impro. You might have seen her recently on stage with  Achtung Improv or International Theater of Stockholm, where she also teaches drop-ins.

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Vad gör vi? 

Vi på Design Lab Sweden genomför kostnadsfria inspirerande öppna workshops. Dessa riktar sig till kreatörer, designers och konstintresserade. Hos oss finner alla en plats där man samlas och gör saker tillsammans i flera olika teman i workshopform.


Organisation

Design Lab Sweden och Stockholm Läns Museum - Slöjd Sthlm

Design Lab Sweden är en ideell organisation som arbetar för att stimulera designintresse och utveckling inom form & design i Sverige. Vi som driver DLS är volontärer och studerar inom konst & design. 


Gästföreläsare 

Olika gästföreläsare vid varje tillfälle 

_____________________________

What we do?

We at Design Lab Sweden carry out free of charge inspirational workshops. These are aimed at creators, designers and artists. With us you will find a place where you can gather and do things together in several different workshop themes.


Organization

Design Lab Sweden and Stockholm Museum - Crafts Sthlm


Design Lab Sweden is a nonprofit organization that works to stimulate design interests and development in form & design in Sweden. We are based in Stockholm.

We who run DLS are volunteers, young professionals and students in art and design.

We are based in Stockholm.


-Our Lab meetings are twice a month. Every other Tuesday -


This group is for you.... 


Who have/are a passionate creative heart, designer, Illustrator etc…. 


Who want to keep inspired 


Who want to share his/her knowledge with other creatives


Who know that our field keeps updating all the time 


Who want to share ideas & connect with new creators. 


Note! 

Since many of us are working or studying. We have planned to hold our workshops at the following time below

Every other Tuesday 18:00 - 21:00

If it’s during weekend 12:00 – 15:00


Contact 

Email claudia@designlabsweden.se 


Stay tuned!

https://www.meetup.com/Design-lab-Sweden/

https://www.facebook.com/designlabsweden2017/ 

https://www.instagram.com/designlabsweden/

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Do you find it challenging to speak Swedish outside of class? Would you like to practice your Swedish in a friendly and safe environment? Are you curious to try a new and fun way of learning? Then this is the workshop for you!

Research shows that laughing makes it easier to learn and remember new information, and one of our favourite ways to laugh is improvised theatre (improv). That is why we have created this group; to provide an opportunity for you to practice your Swedish outside of class, in a new and unconventional way that involves lots of laughing.

Together, we will do different improv games and exercises, in simple Swedish, allowing you to use your current vocabulary as well as expand it further. One of the bases of improv is to ”celebrate your failures” which means that the classes will allow you to make mistakes in a safe environment, so that it’s easier to relax while strengthening your Swedish language muscles!

For those who attend the drop-ins, we would also like to give you the chance to see an improv show and therefore give you a free ticket to one of our ”Improkavalkad” shows in January, played in Swedish.  There will also be occasions when we go out for drinks together after class.

Cost for drop- in classes in January and first class in February: FREE

Mid-February we will start with a class that extends over 6 weeks where we will have themed classes focusing on different specific areas and exercises each week. Examples of themes are: characters, storytelling and being a good listener. 

You do not need any previous theatre or improv experience, however a basic level of understanding and speaking Swedish is required.

Like us on Facebook and don't miss out on cool stuff: https://www.facebook.com/Impro-p%C3%A5-l%C3...

All the best,

Stockholms Improvisationsteater

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
This is a meetup group for the creative people of Stockholm who are looking for companionship of other creatives. We aim for a simple sense of community to begin with, and if people are inspired, perhaps some collaboration can happen.

Meetups are held on a regular basis where we engage in conversations and discussions about a predetermined topic of interest.

People of all creative fields are welcome to join. Whether if you are into creative writing, filmmaking, painting, photography, performing, designing, or just have a general interest in creativity, we would love to meet you. It is a rich mix and makes for a lively meetup!

With a healthy dose of “fika”, we encourage and inspire each other to explore our creativity by fostering a vibrant space that is supportive and non judgmental.

Things to expect:

• A friendly group of supportive people to hang out with on a regular basis.

• A safe environment for new creatives and established ones.

• Fika!

Things that we avoid:

• Judgment calls. This is a friendly community where we can find support and camaraderie.

• Drama. Let's leave the drama in the fictional stories!

If this sounds like a fun interesting group, feel free to join and come to one of our meetings!

P.S. We have a private Facebook group, please join it if you have attended an event.
name: Stockholm Creative People Meetups

description: This group is designed to mediate deeper experiences and understanding of contemporary visual culture. If you're interested in art, but don't always "get it" this group's aim is to contextualize an artwork, performance, or exhibition, through a shared moderated dialogue between members. As a community we may read a text together and discuss it before seeing an exhibition, we may attend a lecture, participate in a workshop, create an object together, any exercise that helps us to more fully appreciate and comprehend visual culture and interdisciplinary practice. We will normally have a "Prep" meetup and then an excursion to go see actual works. Suggestions are welcomed and different members could lead a project, there's no hierarchy. We won't act as museum tour guides or educators, this is a participatory network.

description:
Welcome to a super fun class on improvised singing. It´s just what it sounds like: we create new melodies and lyrics on the spot, using techniques from improv theater and combining it with music theory. This will be two hours of solid fun and constant singing, and you will most definitely break away from your safe zone while making new friends. 

The pianist for this workshop is the fantastic Annika Olsson. Annika has many years of experience working with classes is musical improv. You might for instance have heard and seen her recently in the show Lost in Translation at Boulevardteatern!

Katja Hvenmark-Nilsson has studied musical improv at the Magnet Theater in New York, Improverket and GBG impro. You might have seen her recently on stage with  Achtung Improv or International Theater of Stockholm, where she also teaches drop-ins.

description:
Vad gör vi? 

Vi på Design Lab Sweden genomför kostnadsfria inspirerande öppna workshops. Dessa riktar sig till kreatörer, designers och konstintresserade. Hos oss finner alla en plats där man samlas och gör saker tillsammans i flera olika teman i workshopform.


Organisation

Design Lab Sweden och Stockholm Läns Museum - Slöjd Sthlm

Design Lab Sweden är en ideell organisation som arbetar för att stimulera designintresse och utveckling inom form & design i Sverige. Vi som driver DLS är volontärer och studerar inom konst & design. 


Gästföreläsare 

Olika gästföreläsare vid varje tillfälle 

_____________________________

What we do?

We at Design Lab Sweden carry out free of charge inspirational workshops. These are aimed at creators, designers and artists. With us you will find a place where you can gather and do things together in several different workshop themes.


Organization

Design Lab Sweden and Stockholm Museum - Crafts Sthlm


Design Lab Sweden is a nonprofit organization that works to stimulate design interests and development in form & design in Sweden. We are based in Stockholm.

We who run DLS are volunteers, young professionals and students in art and design.

We are based in Stockholm.


-Our Lab meetings are twice a month. Every other Tuesday -


This group is for you.... 


Who have/are a passionate creative heart, designer, Illustrator etc…. 


Who want to keep inspired 


Who want to share his/her knowledge with other creatives


Who know that our field keeps updating all the time 


Who want to share ideas & connect with new creators. 


Note! 

Since many of us are working or studying. We have planned to hold our workshops at the following time below

Every other Tuesday 18:00 - 21:00

If it’s during weekend 12:00 – 15:00


Contact 

Email claudia@designlabsweden.se 


Stay tuned!

https://www.meetup.com/Design-lab-Sweden/

https://www.facebook.com/designlabsweden2017/ 

https://www.instagram.com/designlabsweden/

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Do you find it challenging to speak Swedish outside of class? Would you like to practice your Swedish in a friendly and safe environment? Are you curious to try a new and fun way of learning? Then this is the workshop for you!

Research shows that laughing makes it easier to learn and remember new information, and one of our favourite ways to laugh is improvised theatre (improv). That is why we have created this group; to provide an opportunity for you to practice your Swedish outside of class, in a new and unconventional way that involves lots of laughing.

Together, we will do different improv games and exercises, in simple Swedish, allowing you to use your current vocabulary as well as expand it further. One of the bases of improv is to ”celebrate your failures” which means that the classes will allow you to make mistakes in a safe environment, so that it’s easier to relax while strengthening your Swedish language muscles!

For those who attend the drop-ins, we would also like to give you the chance to see an improv show and therefore give you a free ticket to one of our ”Improkavalkad” shows in January, played in Swedish.  There will also be occasions when we go out for drinks together after class.

Cost for drop- in classes in January and first class in February: FREE

Mid-February we will start with a class that extends over 6 weeks where we will have themed classes focusing on different specific areas and exercises each week. Examples of themes are: characters, storytelling and being a good listener. 

You do not need any previous theatre or improv experience, however a basic level of understanding and speaking Swedish is required.

Like us on Facebook and don't miss out on cool stuff: https://www.facebook.com/Impro-p%C3%A5-l%C3...

All the best,

Stockholms Improvisationsteater

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
This is a meetup group for the creative people of Stockholm who are looking for companionship of other creatives. We aim for a simple sense of community to begin with, and if people are inspired, perhaps some collaboration can happen.

Meetups are held on a regular basis where we engage in conversations and discussions about a predetermined topic of interest.

People of all creative fields are welcome to join. Whether if you are into creative writing, filmmaking, painting, photography, performing, designing, or just have a general interest in creativity, we would love to meet you. It is a rich mix and makes for a lively meetup!

With a healthy dose of “fika”, we encourage and inspire each other to explore our creativity by fostering a vibrant space that is supportive and non judgmental.

Things to expect:

• A friendly group of supportive people to hang out with on a regular basis.

• A safe environment for new creatives and established ones.

• Fika!

Things that we avoid:

• Judgment calls. This is a friendly community where we can find support and camaraderie.

• Drama. Let's leave the drama in the fictional stories!

If this sounds like a fun interesting group, feel free to join and come to one of our meetings!

P.S. We have a private Facebook group, please join it if you have attended an event.
name: Stockholm Creative People Meetups

category.name: fine arts/culture
description: This group is designed to mediate deeper experiences and understanding of contemporary visual culture. If you're interested in art, but don't always "get it" this group's aim is to contextualize an artwork, performance, or exhibition, through a shared moderated dialogue between members. As a community we may read a text together and discuss it before seeing an exhibition, we may attend a lecture, participate in a workshop, create an object together, any exercise that helps us to more fully appreciate and comprehend visual culture and interdisciplinary practice. We will normally have a "Prep" meetup and then an excursion to go see actual works. Suggestions are welcomed and different members could lead a project, there's no hierarchy. We won't act as museum tour guides or educators, this is a participatory network.

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Welcome to a super fun class on improvised singing. It´s just what it sounds like: we create new melodies and lyrics on the spot, using techniques from improv theater and combining it with music theory. This will be two hours of solid fun and constant singing, and you will most definitely break away from your safe zone while making new friends. 

The pianist for this workshop is the fantastic Annika Olsson. Annika has many years of experience working with classes is musical improv. You might for instance have heard and seen her recently in the show Lost in Translation at Boulevardteatern!

Katja Hvenmark-Nilsson has studied musical improv at the Magnet Theater in New York, Improverket and GBG impro. You might have seen her recently on stage with  Achtung Improv or International Theater of Stockholm, where she also teaches drop-ins.

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Vad gör vi? 

Vi på Design Lab Sweden genomför kostnadsfria inspirerande öppna workshops. Dessa riktar sig till kreatörer, designers och konstintresserade. Hos oss finner alla en plats där man samlas och gör saker tillsammans i flera olika teman i workshopform.


Organisation

Design Lab Sweden och Stockholm Läns Museum - Slöjd Sthlm

Design Lab Sweden är en ideell organisation som arbetar för att stimulera designintresse och utveckling inom form & design i Sverige. Vi som driver DLS är volontärer och studerar inom konst & design. 


Gästföreläsare 

Olika gästföreläsare vid varje tillfälle 

_____________________________

What we do?

We at Design Lab Sweden carry out free of charge inspirational workshops. These are aimed at creators, designers and artists. With us you will find a place where you can gather and do things together in several different workshop themes.


Organization

Design Lab Sweden and Stockholm Museum - Crafts Sthlm


Design Lab Sweden is a nonprofit organization that works to stimulate design interests and development in form & design in Sweden. We are based in Stockholm.

We who run DLS are volunteers, young professionals and students in art and design.

We are based in Stockholm.


-Our Lab meetings are twice a month. Every other Tuesday -


This group is for you.... 


Who have/are a passionate creative heart, designer, Illustrator etc…. 


Who want to keep inspired 


Who want to share his/her knowledge with other creatives


Who know that our field keeps updating all the time 


Who want to share ideas & connect with new creators. 


Note! 

Since many of us are working or studying. We have planned to hold our workshops at the following time below

Every other Tuesday 18:00 - 21:00

If it’s during weekend 12:00 – 15:00


Contact 

Email claudia@designlabsweden.se 


Stay tuned!

https://www.meetup.com/Design-lab-Sweden/

https://www.facebook.com/designlabsweden2017/ 

https://www.instagram.com/designlabsweden/

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Do you find it challenging to speak Swedish outside of class? Would you like to practice your Swedish in a friendly and safe environment? Are you curious to try a new and fun way of learning? Then this is the workshop for you!

Research shows that laughing makes it easier to learn and remember new information, and one of our favourite ways to laugh is improvised theatre (improv). That is why we have created this group; to provide an opportunity for you to practice your Swedish outside of class, in a new and unconventional way that involves lots of laughing.

Together, we will do different improv games and exercises, in simple Swedish, allowing you to use your current vocabulary as well as expand it further. One of the bases of improv is to ”celebrate your failures” which means that the classes will allow you to make mistakes in a safe environment, so that it’s easier to relax while strengthening your Swedish language muscles!

For those who attend the drop-ins, we would also like to give you the chance to see an improv show and therefore give you a free ticket to one of our ”Improkavalkad” shows in January, played in Swedish.  There will also be occasions when we go out for drinks together after class.

Cost for drop- in classes in January and first class in February: FREE

Mid-February we will start with a class that extends over 6 weeks where we will have themed classes focusing on different specific areas and exercises each week. Examples of themes are: characters, storytelling and being a good listener. 

You do not need any previous theatre or improv experience, however a basic level of understanding and speaking Swedish is required.

Like us on Facebook and don't miss out on cool stuff: https://www.facebook.com/Impro-p%C3%A5-l%C3...

All the best,

Stockholms Improvisationsteater

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
The Stockholm Drawing Meetup is a group that has been up and running since April 2015 by volunteers, with the intention of meeting and getting creative together and socialize.

The Stockholm Drawing Meetup’s core goal is to organize art related and fun activities by promoting the cooperation and collaborative work, while keeping in mind constantly the human aspects and needs.

If you like to draw, paint, sketch, etc. or have done so in the past and would like to share the experience in a meetup-setup and have fun at the same time, this group is for you.

This applies to pencil/coal, water color or acrylic/oil or any other medium.

You do not have to be a professional to join but you must have an interest in creating art.

Our members have different concepts of art and participate with different goals. There are members of all the levels, from very beginners, hobbyists to professionals.

In general it is up to you which technique/s or medium to use at every activity.

If you would like to send a particular suggestion for activities or you desire to host an event, don't hesitate to contact any of the co-organizers.

As the group has grown up to reach almost 900 members, from different cultures and backgrounds, it has been considered the need to set up some rules, so that the organization becomes easier and everyone that wants to participate can do it freely, safe and comfortably.

Please read carefully our organization policy and its updatings sited at the forum, and make sure this is something you are prepared to abide:

https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51143584

https://www.meetup.com/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51306390

Thanks! <3

description:
This is a group for anyone interested in Interior Design, Decoration, and Architecture. The aim of the group is to form a creative network that helps each other to grow professionally, socially, and individually. 

Interior Design and Architecture touches a broad spectrum of fields ranging from product design, photography, and graphics, to sustainability, well-being, and psychology. Not only will we discuss new trends in design and grow intellectually, but also develop artistic skills by engaging in creative activities together. 

If you are creative and interested in Interior Design and Architecture - let’s connect and have some fun!

description:
Vad gör vi? 

Vi på Design Lab Sweden genomför kostnadsfria inspirerande öppna workshops. Dessa riktar sig till kreatörer, designers och konstintresserade. Hos oss finner alla en plats där man samlas och gör saker tillsammans i flera olika teman i workshopform.


Organisation

Design Lab Sweden och Stockholm Läns Museum - Slöjd Sthlm

Design Lab Sweden är en ideell organisation som arbetar för att stimulera designintresse och utveckling inom form & design i Sverige. Vi som driver DLS är volontärer och studerar inom konst & design. 


Gästföreläsare 

Olika gästföreläsare vid varje tillfälle 

_____________________________

What we do?

We at Design Lab Sweden carry out free of charge inspirational workshops. These are aimed at creators, designers and artists. With us you will find a place where you can gather and do things together in several different workshop themes.


Organization

Design Lab Sweden and Stockholm Museum - Crafts Sthlm


Design Lab Sweden is a nonprofit organization that works to stimulate design interests and development in form & design in Sweden. We are based in Stockholm.

We who run DLS are volunteers, young professionals and students in art and design.

We are based in Stockholm.


-Our Lab meetings are twice a month. Every other Tuesday -


This group is for you.... 


Who have/are a passionate creative heart, designer, Illustrator etc…. 


Who want to keep inspired 


Who want to share his/her knowledge with other creatives


Who know that our field keeps updating all the time 


Who want to share ideas & connect with new creators. 


Note! 

Since many of us are working or studying. We have planned to hold our workshops at the following time below

Every other Tuesday 18:00 - 21:00

If it’s during weekend 12:00 – 15:00


Contact 

Email claudia@designlabsweden.se 


Stay tuned!

https://www.meetup.com/Design-lab-Sweden/

https://www.facebook.com/designlabsweden2017/ 

https://www.instagram.com/designlabsweden/

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Do you find it challenging to speak Swedish outside of class? Would you like to practice your Swedish in a friendly and safe environment? Are you curious to try a new and fun way of learning? Then this is the workshop for you!

Research shows that laughing makes it easier to learn and remember new information, and one of our favourite ways to laugh is improvised theatre (improv). That is why we have created this group; to provide an opportunity for you to practice your Swedish outside of class, in a new and unconventional way that involves lots of laughing.

Together, we will do different improv games and exercises, in simple Swedish, allowing you to use your current vocabulary as well as expand it further. One of the bases of improv is to ”celebrate your failures” which means that the classes will allow you to make mistakes in a safe environment, so that it’s easier to relax while strengthening your Swedish language muscles!

For those who attend the drop-ins, we would also like to give you the chance to see an improv show and therefore give you a free ticket to one of our ”Improkavalkad” shows in January, played in Swedish.  There will also be occasions when we go out for drinks together after class.

Cost for drop- in classes in January and first class in February: FREE

Mid-February we will start with a class that extends over 6 weeks where we will have themed classes focusing on different specific areas and exercises each week. Examples of themes are: characters, storytelling and being a good listener. 

You do not need any previous theatre or improv experience, however a basic level of understanding and speaking Swedish is required.

Like us on Facebook and don't miss out on cool stuff: https://www.facebook.com/Impro-p%C3%A5-l%C3...

All the best,

Stockholms Improvisationsteater

description:
The Stockholm Drawing Meetup is a group that has been up and running since April 2015 by volunteers, with the intention of meeting and getting creative together and socialize.

The Stockholm Drawing Meetup’s core goal is to organize art related and fun activities by promoting the cooperation and collaborative work, while keeping in mind constantly the human aspects and needs.

If you like to draw, paint, sketch, etc. or have done so in the past and would like to share the experience in a meetup-setup and have fun at the same time, this group is for you.

This applies to pencil/coal, water color or acrylic/oil or any other medium.

You do not have to be a professional to join but you must have an interest in creating art.

Our members have different concepts of art and participate with different goals. There are members of all the levels, from very beginners, hobbyists to professionals.

In general it is up to you which technique/s or medium to use at every activity.

If you would like to send a particular suggestion for activities or you desire to host an event, don't hesitate to contact any of the co-organizers.

As the group has grown up to reach almost 900 members, from different cultures and backgrounds, it has been considered the need to set up some rules, so that the organization becomes easier and everyone that wants to participate can do it freely, safe and comfortably.

Please read carefully our organization policy and its updatings sited at the forum, and make sure this is something you are prepared to abide:

https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51143584

https://www.meetup.com/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51306390

Thanks! <3

description:
This is a meetup group for the creative people of Stockholm who are looking for companionship of other creatives. We aim for a simple sense of community to begin with, and if people are inspired, perhaps some collaboration can happen.

Meetups are held on a regular basis where we engage in conversations and discussions about a predetermined topic of interest.

People of all creative fields are welcome to join. Whether if you are into creative writing, filmmaking, painting, photography, performing, designing, or just have a general interest in creativity, we would love to meet you. It is a rich mix and makes for a lively meetup!

With a healthy dose of “fika”, we encourage and inspire each other to explore our creativity by fostering a vibrant space that is supportive and non judgmental.

Things to expect:

• A friendly group of supportive people to hang out with on a regular basis.

• A safe environment for new creatives and established ones.

• Fika!

Things that we avoid:

• Judgment calls. This is a friendly community where we can find support and camaraderie.

• Drama. Let's leave the drama in the fictional stories!

If this sounds like a fun interesting group, feel free to join and come to one of our meetings!

P.S. We have a private Facebook group, please join it if you have attended an event.
name: Stockholm Creative People Meetups

category.name: fine arts/culture
description: This group is designed to mediate deeper experiences and understanding of contemporary visual culture. If you're interested in art, but don't always "get it" this group's aim is to contextualize an artwork, performance, or exhibition, through a shared moderated dialogue between members. As a community we may read a text together and discuss it before seeing an exhibition, we may attend a lecture, participate in a workshop, create an object together, any exercise that helps us to more fully appreciate and comprehend visual culture and interdisciplinary practice. We will normally have a "Prep" meetup and then an excursion to go see actual works. Suggestions are welcomed and different members could lead a project, there's no hierarchy. We won't act as museum tour guides or educators, this is a participatory network.

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Welcome to a super fun class on improvised singing. It´s just what it sounds like: we create new melodies and lyrics on the spot, using techniques from improv theater and combining it with music theory. This will be two hours of solid fun and constant singing, and you will most definitely break away from your safe zone while making new friends. 

The pianist for this workshop is the fantastic Annika Olsson. Annika has many years of experience working with classes is musical improv. You might for instance have heard and seen her recently in the show Lost in Translation at Boulevardteatern!

Katja Hvenmark-Nilsson has studied musical improv at the Magnet Theater in New York, Improverket and GBG impro. You might have seen her recently on stage with  Achtung Improv or International Theater of Stockholm, where she also teaches drop-ins.

Bring your own idea or project to get feedback from the QueensLab Community or just bring your laptop and your skills to help others.

RULES ARE - All code and design developed during the Lab is free to use for any participant and all content will be shared with you.

Some nights we will work on predefined projects - some nights we will grab your idea and make it happen.

Welcome!

<br>

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
The Stockholm Drawing Meetup is a group that has been up and running since April 2015 by volunteers, with the intention of meeting and getting creative together and socialize.

The Stockholm Drawing Meetup’s core goal is to organize art related and fun activities by promoting the cooperation and collaborative work, while keeping in mind constantly the human aspects and needs.

If you like to draw, paint, sketch, etc. or have done so in the past and would like to share the experience in a meetup-setup and have fun at the same time, this group is for you.

This applies to pencil/coal, water color or acrylic/oil or any other medium.

You do not have to be a professional to join but you must have an interest in creating art.

Our members have different concepts of art and participate with different goals. There are members of all the levels, from very beginners, hobbyists to professionals.

In general it is up to you which technique/s or medium to use at every activity.

If you would like to send a particular suggestion for activities or you desire to host an event, don't hesitate to contact any of the co-organizers.

As the group has grown up to reach almost 900 members, from different cultures and backgrounds, it has been considered the need to set up some rules, so that the organization becomes easier and everyone that wants to participate can do it freely, safe and comfortably.

Please read carefully our organization policy and its updatings sited at the forum, and make sure this is something you are prepared to abide:

https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51143584

https://www.meetup.com/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51306390

Thanks! <3

description:
This is a group for anyone interested in Interior Design, Decoration, and Architecture. The aim of the group is to form a creative network that helps each other to grow professionally, socially, and individually. 

Interior Design and Architecture touches a broad spectrum of fields ranging from product design, photography, and graphics, to sustainability, well-being, and psychology. Not only will we discuss new trends in design and grow intellectually, but also develop artistic skills by engaging in creative activities together. 

If you are creative and interested in Interior Design and Architecture - let’s connect and have some fun!

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
This is a meetup group for the creative people of Stockholm who are looking for companionship of other creatives. We aim for a simple sense of community to begin with, and if people are inspired, perhaps some collaboration can happen.

Meetups are held on a regular basis where we engage in conversations and discussions about a predetermined topic of interest.

People of all creative fields are welcome to join. Whether if you are into creative writing, filmmaking, painting, photography, performing, designing, or just have a general interest in creativity, we would love to meet you. It is a rich mix and makes for a lively meetup!

With a healthy dose of “fika”, we encourage and inspire each other to explore our creativity by fostering a vibrant space that is supportive and non judgmental.

Things to expect:

• A friendly group of supportive people to hang out with on a regular basis.

• A safe environment for new creatives and established ones.

• Fika!

Things that we avoid:

• Judgment calls. This is a friendly community where we can find support and camaraderie.

• Drama. Let's leave the drama in the fictional stories!

If this sounds like a fun interesting group, feel free to join and come to one of our meetings!

P.S. We have a private Facebook group, please join it if you have attended an event.
name: Stockholm Creative People Meetups

category.name: fine arts/culture
description: This group is designed to mediate deeper experiences and understanding of contemporary visual culture. If you're interested in art, but don't always "get it" this group's aim is to contextualize an artwork, performance, or exhibition, through a shared moderated dialogue between members. As a community we may read a text together and discuss it before seeing an exhibition, we may attend a lecture, participate in a workshop, create an object together, any exercise that helps us to more fully appreciate and comprehend visual culture and interdisciplinary practice. We will normally have a "Prep" meetup and then an excursion to go see actual works. Suggestions are welcomed and different members could lead a project, there's no hierarchy. We won't act as museum tour guides or educators, this is a participatory network.
name: Visual Culture

description:
Welcome to a super fun class on improvised singing. It´s just what it sounds like: we create new melodies and lyrics on the spot, using techniques from improv theater and combining it with music theory. This will be two hours of solid fun and constant singing, and you will most definitely break away from your safe zone while making new friends. 

The pianist for this workshop is the fantastic Annika Olsson. Annika has many years of experience working with classes is musical improv. You might for instance have heard and seen her recently in the show Lost in Translation at Boulevardteatern!

Katja Hvenmark-Nilsson has studied musical improv at the Magnet Theater in New York, Improverket and GBG impro. You might have seen her recently on stage with  Achtung Improv or International Theater of Stockholm, where she also teaches drop-ins.
name: Learn to improvise songs!

description:
Vad gör vi? 

Vi på Design Lab Sweden genomför kostnadsfria inspirerande öppna workshops. Dessa riktar sig till kreatörer, designers och konstintresserade. Hos oss finner alla en plats där man samlas och gör saker tillsammans i flera olika teman i workshopform.


Organisation

Design Lab Sweden och Stockholm Läns Museum - Slöjd Sthlm

Design Lab Sweden är en ideell organisation som arbetar för att stimulera designintresse och utveckling inom form & design i Sverige. Vi som driver DLS är volontärer och studerar inom konst & design. 


Gästföreläsare 

Olika gästföreläsare vid varje tillfälle 

_____________________________

What we do?

We at Design Lab Sweden carry out free of charge inspirational workshops. These are aimed at creators, designers and artists. With us you will find a place where you can gather and do things together in several different workshop themes.


Organization

Design Lab Sweden and Stockholm Museum - Crafts Sthlm


Design Lab Sweden is a nonprofit organization that works to stimulate design interests and development in form & design in Sweden. We are based in Stockholm.

We who run DLS are volunteers, young professionals and students in art and design.

We are based in Stockholm.


-Our Lab meetings are twice a month. Every other Tuesday -


This group is for you.... 


Who have/are a passionate creative heart, designer, Illustrator etc…. 


Who want to keep inspired 


Who want to share his/her knowledge with other creatives


Who know that our field keeps updating all the time 


Who want to share ideas & connect with new creators. 


Note! 

Since many of us are working or studying. We have planned to hold our workshops at the following time below

Every other Tuesday 18:00 - 21:00

If it’s during weekend 12:00 – 15:00


Contact 

Email claudia@designlabsweden.se 


Stay tuned!

https://www.meetup.com/Design-lab-Sweden/

https://www.facebook.com/designlabsweden2017/ 

https://www.instagram.com/designlabsweden/

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
Do you find it challenging to speak Swedish outside of class? Would you like to practice your Swedish in a friendly and safe environment? Are you curious to try a new and fun way of learning? Then this is the workshop for you!

Research shows that laughing makes it easier to learn and remember new information, and one of our favourite ways to laugh is improvised theatre (improv). That is why we have created this group; to provide an opportunity for you to practice your Swedish outside of class, in a new and unconventional way that involves lots of laughing.

Together, we will do different improv games and exercises, in simple Swedish, allowing you to use your current vocabulary as well as expand it further. One of the bases of improv is to ”celebrate your failures” which means that the classes will allow you to make mistakes in a safe environment, so that it’s easier to relax while strengthening your Swedish language muscles!

For those who attend the drop-ins, we would also like to give you the chance to see an improv show and therefore give you a free ticket to one of our ”Improkavalkad” shows in January, played in Swedish.  There will also be occasions when we go out for drinks together after class.

Cost for drop- in classes in January and first class in February: FREE

Mid-February we will start with a class that extends over 6 weeks where we will have themed classes focusing on different specific areas and exercises each week. Examples of themes are: characters, storytelling and being a good listener. 

You do not need any previous theatre or improv experience, however a basic level of understanding and speaking Swedish is required.

Like us on Facebook and don't miss out on cool stuff: https://www.facebook.com/Impro-p%C3%A5-l%C3...

All the best,

Stockholms Improvisationsteater

description:
The Stockholm Drawing Meetup is a group that has been up and running since April 2015 by volunteers, with the intention of meeting and getting creative together and socialize.

The Stockholm Drawing Meetup’s core goal is to organize art related and fun activities by promoting the cooperation and collaborative work, while keeping in mind constantly the human aspects and needs.

If you like to draw, paint, sketch, etc. or have done so in the past and would like to share the experience in a meetup-setup and have fun at the same time, this group is for you.

This applies to pencil/coal, water color or acrylic/oil or any other medium.

You do not have to be a professional to join but you must have an interest in creating art.

Our members have different concepts of art and participate with different goals. There are members of all the levels, from very beginners, hobbyists to professionals.

In general it is up to you which technique/s or medium to use at every activity.

If you would like to send a particular suggestion for activities or you desire to host an event, don't hesitate to contact any of the co-organizers.

As the group has grown up to reach almost 900 members, from different cultures and backgrounds, it has been considered the need to set up some rules, so that the organization becomes easier and everyone that wants to participate can do it freely, safe and comfortably.

Please read carefully our organization policy and its updatings sited at the forum, and make sure this is something you are prepared to abide:

https://www.meetup.com/es-ES/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51143584

https://www.meetup.com/Stockholm-Drawing-Meetup/messages/boards/thread/51306390

Thanks! <3

description:
This is a group for anyone interested in Interior Design, Decoration, and Architecture. The aim of the group is to form a creative network that helps each other to grow professionally, socially, and individually. 

Interior Design and Architecture touches a broad spectrum of fields ranging from product design, photography, and graphics, to sustainability, well-being, and psychology. Not only will we discuss new trends in design and grow intellectually, but also develop artistic skills by engaging in creative activities together. 

If you are creative and interested in Interior Design and Architecture - let’s connect and have some fun!

category.name: fine arts/culture
description:
This is a meetup group for the creative people of Stockholm who are looking for companionship of other creatives. We aim for a simple sense of community to begin with, and if people are inspired, perhaps some collaboration can happen.

Meetups are held on a regular basis where we engage in conversations and discussions about a predetermined topic of interest.

People of all creative fields are welcome to join. Whether if you are into creative writing, filmmaking, painting, photography, performing, designing, or just have a general interest in creativity, we would love to meet you. It is a rich mix and makes for a lively meetup!

With a healthy dose of “fika”, we encourage and inspire each other to explore our creativity by fostering a vibrant space that is supportive and non judgmental.

Things to expect:

• A friendly group of supportive people to hang out with on a regular basis.

• A safe environment for new creatives and established ones.

• Fika!

Things that we avoid:

• Judgment calls. This is a friendly community where we can find support and camaraderie.

• Drama. Let's leave the drama in the fictional stories!

If this sounds like a fun interesting group, feel free to join and come to one of our meetings!

P.S. We have a private Facebook group, please join it if you have attended an event.
